Description:
ALL SET UP AND READY TO GO!
Located in the ever popular township of Bass with views of the rolling hills and only a short drive to Melbourne and Kilcunda is this remarkable 5 acre property.
Perfectly set up for horses with 7 individual stables, ample shedding, quality fencing and the paddocks are flat.
The farmhouse comes complete with 4 bedrooms, spacious living area, well appointed bathroom and kitchen, outdoor undercover area plus the added bonus of a separate bungalow.
We are seeking the right person to love this very special property.
Call for a private inspection today.
For weekly up-dates, including addresses of properties or more information, join our Buyers Club, visit: www.pbe***

Address: CA 64C Coast Road French Island VIC 3921
Description:
Executors Sale by Expressions of Interest closing 29th April
"Bonnievale"
25 acres of wilderness with licensed access surrounded by French Island National Park and only 1 km to ferry.
Although this property has been vacant since the bushfires of the late 1930s, it has a long and rich history of occupation
going right back to the 1890's - check out our information memorandum for details.
The entrance point off Coast Road was pegged and a path surveyed through the National Park to the South West Corner of the property
along the proposed access alignment. A permit to build a dwelling is available (STGA).
To obtain a full history of the site together with a report on the planning provisions and options for preserving the park or to inspect this unique property
contact Phil Bock on 0438 497 715 or Chris Watt 0417 588 321 for further information and to obtain expression of interest documentation.
Our Vendor has received an offer of $90,000 which will be accepted upon closure of Expressions of Interest in the absence of any higher offer.
Interested parties who are willing to better this offer must submit a signed Expression of Interest form to the agency by 5:00pm on Friday April 29th.
If there are no offers above $90,000 the property will be sold to the purchasers who have already communicated their interest without further correspondence.
It there are offers above $90,000 the 3 highest offerors will be provided with a Contract of Sale and Section 32 Statement in their name and invited to submit their walk away price within 7 days. The 10% deposit will be payable upon acceptance of the highest offer as evidenced by the execution of a Contract of Sale by the Vendor.
Good luck to all.

Description:
SOLD
Ready to move straight in, this light and bright newly renovated 3BR waterfront cottage on 508m2 (approx) is located in a peaceful neighbourhood and provides direct access to the beach. Whether you are in the market as a first home buyer or looking for a perfect holiday home or investment property, this rare opportunity will not be on the market for long.
Conveniently located just off the Bass Highway only 1¼hr from Melbourne, this private and charming home features three bedrooms with wall to wall carpets, master with sparkling new ensuite, open plan living/dining/kitchen with split system and ceiling fan, a stylish electric oven and curved glass rangehood and modern light fixtures throughout. On a well maintained block, the covered rear deck provides the perfect space for alfresco dining or a lazy breakfast looking out over the water while you read the paper listening only to the birds. Added features include a 1000L rainwater tank and a quirky shipping container as a secure backyard shed alternative.
A leisurely stroll along the beachfront provides breathtaking views of French Island while the home itself is located only minutes from the Grantville shopping precinct which has all your needs accommodated. The region is rich with places to explore including the award winning Bass River Winery, Bassine Specialty Cheeses, local farmers markets and, of course, all there is to see and do in Phillip Island and along the popular Bass Coast. You will need to act quickly to secure this opportunity.
Suit $299,000 plus buyers.

Description:
Deceased Estate
Genuine Vendors want to sell this very well presented, house sized, three bedroom unit which is set a hop skip and a jump to Lang Lang township, shops and Primary School.
The fixtures and fittings include a built in wall oven and separate griller, electric hotplates, dishwasher, exhaust rangehood, and a reverse cycle heating and cooling unit.
The master bedroom has a walk in robe and an ensuite and is set apart from the other two well appointed bedrooms (both with large BIR's and one with shelves as well).
Central to the home is a generous sized living room, with ceiling fan. A large defined dining area and a breakfast bar bench to the kitchen.
A family bathroom with bath, shower and hand basin is set close to the other two bedrooms and a separate toilet and laundry complete the interior list.
Good quality curtains throughout the house.
Extra bonuses are an undercover entertainment area which adjoins the dining area and perfect for family bar-b-ques.
There is an oversized double lock up garage with remote control and internal access. The back yard is fully enclosed and easy to maintain.
One of four units, this one is set at the rear of the allotment making it quite private and separated from the others and it doesn't share any common walls.
Currently there is no active Owners Corporation, just an annual cost of the Building and Common Area Insurance.

Description:
Prestigious Horse Property/Business Opportunity
Kaye Charles Real Estate are proud to present to market for our motivated vendor one of the region's most remarkable equine Estates - "Westernport", a tailored 97 acres approx. with the title fronting waterline and ornamental lake. Located within minutes to Pakenham Park Racing Precinct (convenient for horse enthusiasts).
Offering views of Western Port Bay is this near new, Victorian inspired, 6 star mini mansion, designed and built by the award winning "Harkaway Homes." The 2 story residence, with full verandas and balcony commands the highest level of grandeur whilst providing an irreplaceable living environment of rare sophistication and opulence. All principal rooms are positioned to take in the magnificent horizon, made even more dramatic through double glazed, full length windows, capturing the view and an abundance of light.
The 53 sq. floor plan is as sophisticated as it is practical, designed to accommodate 2 families with 5 bedrooms, offering the perfect balance of formal and casual living. The lower Level offers a more casual setting with fully equipped kitchen complete with walk in pantry, incorporating family room with separate, formal lounge, powder room, 2 bedrooms and bathroom. The lift, or stairs lead to the 2nd level, offering a more elevated level of luxury. The designer, stone kitchen with Falcon cooking and butler's pantry is the focal point of the home, overlooking spacious living room with gas log fire. Cafe doors fold open to the magnificent Coolgardie indoor/outdoor entertaining room complete with built in BBQ and wok burner set in a stone bench top, with separate bar, all making for a serene, relaxed setting. The parent's retreat is a plush space that enjoys full ensuite and walk in robes. Indoors has been appointed with every conceivable luxury from hard wood, polished floor boards throughout, 3 fully tiled, travertine bathrooms with stone bench tops, 4 toilets, high, decorative ceilings, refrigerated cooling, a generous mud room/laundry, storage galore and much more. A second, 2 bedroom residence would be ideal as a care takers residence, a comfortable home for a 2nd family or guest retreat, boasting kitchen, bathroom, heating and cooling.
Outdoors has been tailored for thoroughbred's but would accommodate all stock. Improvements include bitumen drive, 4 car garage, over 20 horse paddocks with post and rail fencing, 8 lined shelters, stable complex, large, lock up machinery shed, round yard, electronic gate with security pad, full irrigation and beautifully manicured gardens. Over 300 metres of beach frontage, showcasing panoramic views of French Island, Author's Seat and beyond makes for truly exceptional real estate.
The property offers the fortunate buyer a potentially lucrative business opportunity through multiple revenue streams. One prospect is horse agistment, with the current owner offering to lease back paddocks for an indefinite period, generating approximately $52,000 P.A. The property also lends itself to being run as a B&B, wedding reception/function centre or farm stays. The possibilities are endless.
Contact Amanda Charles - 0400 347 968

Description:
WATERFRONT PROPERTY - THE ESSENCE OF STYLE
This impressively appointed, architect designed, rendered brick, foreshore residence features -
* 4 generous bedrooms
* Master with bay views, walk-in-robe and sumptuous ensuite
* Elevated living and meals area
* Free flowing kitchen with island bench/breakfast bar and quality stainless steel fittings
* Gas log fire, central heating and cooling
* Surprise hidden secret door leading to quaint outlook
* Full height windows to maximise the magic water views and light
* 2nd living room or sitting area
* Powder room
* Quality family bathroom
* Plenty of linen and storage cupboards
* Neutral tones throughout
* 4 square garage including single remote door for access to backyard
* Huge storage under approx.15 sqm.
* Rendered brick exterior
* Low maintenance gardens
All this and more situated on a large foreshore block of approx. 1,013 sqm. There is little to do except sit back and enjoy this tranquil slice of Westernport Bay in luxury for many years to come. Only approx. 25 mins to Phillip Island and major shopping centre, approx. 8 mins to cafes, doctor, chemist, wineries and approx. 1 hr 20 mins to CBD with dual lane highway.

Description:
PERFECTLY PRESENTED - NEAR BEACH !
Delightfully situated in a court location close to shops and cafes and set on a large 1200 sqm approx block, this immaculate 4 bedroom brick home comprises spacious living area with split-system aircon, sunny meals area with entry to undercover paved bbq area with which expands your entertainment options, cosy kitchen with electric cooking, all bedrooms with BIR/s and carpeted, master with walk-in robe and ensuite, family bathroom with full bath and separate shower, plenty of cupboard space and a good size laundry.
The very spacious backyard, with well manicured garden, has a gate entry at the back of the yard to crown land through which you can walk to the water which is only metres away from the property.
The long driveway and double garage, which is concreted and powered, give plenty of room for those extra vehicles. Just from pulling up out the front you can see that this is a much loved property and well cared for by the owners.
Walk to the shops and VLine bus service at end of court. Major shopping centre and Phillip Island approx. 25 mins away and CBD approx. 1 hr 20 mins viah dual lane highway.

Description:
Olde meets new
Set on a large 735sqm (approx.) block in a quiet street, this warm and inviting home is sure to attract a variety of potential buyers. A neat path leads you to the front door and sets the scene for the interior with a host of original features, from the timber floors, to the doors and the ceilings. Four comfortable bedrooms, family room and renovated kitchen makes for comfortable family living. The renovations to the home add a touch of class with modern bathroom, ensuite and walk through robes. Split system air con and a gas heater take care of comfort both summer and winter. The established gardens, complete with garden shed and rear lane access provide ample space for fun or entertaining. The large covered entertainers deck is the perfect setting for a barbecue, party or just a quiet glass of wine at the end of the day. Fully fenced and just a very short stroll to shops, school and transport. An inspection will not disappoint.

Description:
BAY VIEWS ! SWIMMING POOL ! LARGE BLOCK !
Positioned in a quiet court location with quality homes surrounding this immaculate 3 bedroom home offers so much for money. Featuring open plan lounge/formal dining area with sliding door to entertainment deck with bay views, split-system airconditioner, cosy kitchen offering some bay views, meals area with sliding door to deck, BIRs in two bedrooms with wwc, master having ensuite and walk-in-robe and family bathroom with separate shower and bath. If you love entertaining or just relaxing with minimal maintenance you will absolutely appreciate this backyard with extensive timber decking of walkways and sun lounge areas, gazebo and pool. The property is situated on a block approx.. 935 sq.m. with circular driveway, plenty of room for caravan, boat or extra vehicles and yard is fully fenced.
A 24 hour boat ramp/jetty is only a few minutes away, local shop, community centre, tennis courts, lawn bowls, v-line and school bus stops. Visit the local wineries and cafes approx.. 7 mins and a major shopping centre and Phillip Island approx.. 25mins. The vendor will also leave some furniture.
